WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.112 --> 00:00:04.381
(dark. dramatic music)

2
00:00:11.623 --> 00:00:13.658
(gun being loaded)

3
00:00:21.533 --> 00:00:23.601
(gun cocked)

4
00:00:26.704 --> 00:00:28.740
(faint whooshing of traffic)

5
00:00:42.152 --> 00:00:44.354
(bright. bossa nova-style music)

6
00:00:45.924 --> 00:00:47.124
Um...

7
00:00:58.803 --> 00:01:00.237
Hm...

8
00:01:00.270 --> 00:01:02.640
What about chocolate?

9
00:01:03.875 --> 00:01:06.209
Okay. you can get it.

10
00:01:08.345 --> 00:01:09.279
This?

11
00:01:09.313 --> 00:01:11.049
No. baby. that is enough.

12
00:01:11.081 --> 00:01:12.750
Come on. Scooter.

13
00:01:12.784 --> 00:01:13.818
-Hello.
-Hello.

14
00:01:13.851 --> 00:01:14.852
Hello.

15
00:01:16.486 --> 00:01:17.822
Okay.

16
00:01:19.122 --> 00:01:21.325
(scanner beeping)

17
00:01:24.862 --> 00:01:27.599
You can help me out with this.

18
00:01:27.632 --> 00:01:28.967
I'll just put...

19
00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:30.702
like that.

20
00:01:39.644 --> 00:01:41.012
How much is it?

21
00:01:41.045 --> 00:01:42.312
(tapping. register beeps)

22
00:01:42.346 --> 00:01:45.550
Okay. here we go. 30.

23
00:01:46.985 --> 00:01:47.885
Thank you.

24
00:01:47.919 --> 00:01:49.887
(register clacking)

25
00:01:49.921 --> 00:01:51.321
-Mom. can you help me?
-Mm-hm.

26
00:01:51.355 --> 00:01:53.958
I'll help you
to hurry up a bit.

27
00:01:53.992 --> 00:01:55.125
(plastic crinkling)

28
00:01:55.158 --> 00:01:56.628
Like this.

29
00:01:57.929 --> 00:02:00.297
(indistinct)

30
00:02:00.330 --> 00:02:01.666
Bye!

31
00:02:01.699 --> 00:02:02.432
Mwah!

32
00:02:02.466 --> 00:02:04.201
-Bye-bye. thank you.
-Bye-bye.

33
00:02:08.940 --> 00:02:10.140
(he sighs)

34
00:02:26.991 --> 00:02:29.292
Can I now eat chocolates?

35
00:02:29.326 --> 00:02:31.395
No. honey. later.

36
00:02:31.428 --> 00:02:32.063
Okay.

37
00:02:32.096 --> 00:02:33.865
(ominous music)

38
00:02:33.898 --> 00:02:35.399
(chuckling)

39
00:02:38.036 --> 00:02:40.938
(blade rasps)

40
00:02:40.972 --> 00:02:41.773
Mama!

41
00:02:41.806 --> 00:02:43.608
-(screaming)
-(grunts)

42
00:02:43.641 --> 00:02:46.144
(tense music)

43
00:02:46.176 --> 00:02:47.745
(coughing)

44
00:02:47.779 --> 00:02:49.681
Mom! Mom!

45
00:02:49.714 --> 00:02:51.849
Mom!

46
00:02:51.883 --> 00:02:54.619
-(faint whimper)
-Mom!

47
00:02:54.652 --> 00:02:56.921
Mom. Please. please.

48
00:02:58.790 --> 00:03:00.591
Mom!

49
00:03:00.625 --> 00:03:02.627
(whimpers)

50
00:03:02.660 --> 00:03:03.661
Mom!

51
00:03:05.963 --> 00:03:07.732
Mom.

52
00:03:07.765 --> 00:03:10.001
Mom. Mom!

53
00:03:10.034 --> 00:03:11.969
Mom! Mom!

54
00:03:12.003 --> 00:03:14.839
Mom. please!

55
00:03:14.872 --> 00:03:17.340
(faint whimpering)

56
00:03:17.374 --> 00:03:19.577
(fanfare-like broadcast music)

57
00:03:21.311 --> 00:03:23.047
The nation is gripped by fear

58
00:03:23.081 --> 00:03:25.415
as a wave of shock
sweeps the country.

59
00:03:25.449 --> 00:03:27.317
A mother was murdered
in broad daylight

60
00:03:27.350 --> 00:03:28.452
in front of her child

61
00:03:28.485 --> 00:03:31.556
by another suspected
undocumented migrant.

62
00:03:31.589 --> 00:03:34.592
Parents are afraid to let
their children play outside.

63
00:03:34.625 --> 00:03:38.696
and many women avoid venturing
out after dark altogether.

64
00:03:38.730 --> 00:03:40.732
(tense. ponderous music)

65
00:03:50.675 --> 00:03:52.677
(staticky blips)

66
00:04:34.118 --> 00:04:35.418
But in a twist
that has captured

67
00:04:35.452 --> 00:04:37.387
the imagination
of the public.

68
00:04:37.420 --> 00:04:39.857
hope doesn't rest in the hands
of government officials

69
00:04:39.891 --> 00:04:41.324
or law enforcement.

70
00:04:41.358 --> 00:04:44.061
Instead. it lies
with an enigmatic figure.

71
00:04:44.095 --> 00:04:45.563
the vigilante citizen

72
00:04:45.596 --> 00:04:47.265
who's delivering
a brand of justice

73
00:04:47.297 --> 00:04:48.900
that some believe
the authorities

74
00:04:48.933 --> 00:04:50.467
have failed to provide.

75
00:04:50.501 --> 00:04:52.937
targeting both criminals
and those in power

76
00:04:52.970 --> 00:04:56.207
accused of allowing crime
to flourish unchecked.

77
00:04:56.240 --> 00:04:57.542
We took to the streets

78
00:04:57.575 --> 00:05:00.011
to hear what people think
about the shadowy figure.

79
00:05:00.044 --> 00:05:01.712
Here's what they had to say.

80
00:05:01.746 --> 00:05:02.947
He's a real hero.

81
00:05:02.980 --> 00:05:05.983
You know. we work.
we pay taxes. and for what?

82
00:05:06.017 --> 00:05:08.219
To help all of Africa?

83
00:05:08.252 --> 00:05:10.955
You see. they come here
and we pay for them.

84
00:05:10.988 --> 00:05:12.757
and in return.
we get robbed.

85
00:05:12.790 --> 00:05:13.691
And. as a woman.

86
00:05:13.724 --> 00:05:16.294
you cannot go out
after 9 p.m. anymore.

87
00:05:16.326 --> 00:05:18.229
No. it's too risky.

88
00:05:18.262 --> 00:05:19.362
I love that guy.

89
00:05:19.396 --> 00:05:20.430
He goes out there.

90
00:05:20.463 --> 00:05:21.933
he goes against
all those criminals.

91
00:05:21.966 --> 00:05:25.036
They laugh about the police
but not about him.

92
00:05:25.069 --> 00:05:26.403
Uh. I wanna marry him.

93
00:05:26.436 --> 00:05:29.674
I mean. he's a real knight.
and he helps the helpless.

94
00:05:29.707 --> 00:05:33.343
The individual continues
his vigilante form of justice.

95
00:05:33.376 --> 00:05:35.445
claiming the police
and judicial systems

96
00:05:35.478 --> 00:05:37.748
are failing to protect
the public.

97
00:05:37.782 --> 00:05:38.950
Last week.

98
00:05:38.983 --> 00:05:41.418
the leader of a prominent
Middle Eastern crime syndicate.

99
00:05:41.451 --> 00:05:42.787
along with his associate.

100
00:05:42.820 --> 00:05:45.756
were discovered dead
in a dumpster.

101
00:05:45.790 --> 00:05:46.858
(click. chime)

102
00:05:46.891 --> 00:05:48.659
That guy out there? Wow.

103
00:05:48.693 --> 00:05:51.863
Have you heard of this
vigilante crime-fighter guy

104
00:05:51.896 --> 00:05:53.030
over in Europe?

105
00:05:53.064 --> 00:05:55.566
He's. like. the real deal.

106
00:05:55.600 --> 00:05:57.034
This man is taking out
the trash.

107
00:05:57.068 --> 00:06:00.838
I think we need somebody over
here in the States like that.

108
00:06:00.872 --> 00:06:01.839
What do you guys think?

109
00:06:01.873 --> 00:06:03.174
Comment down below.
let me know.

110
00:06:03.207 --> 00:06:05.009
(click. chime)

111
00:06:05.042 --> 00:06:07.078
(engine rumbling)

112
00:06:07.111 --> 00:06:09.113
(tense rhythmic music)

113
00:06:15.286 --> 00:06:16.988
(burst of static)

114
00:06:17.021 --> 00:06:19.489
(clicking)

115
00:06:19.523 --> 00:06:20.758
There's been a lot said
about me.

116
00:06:20.791 --> 00:06:23.594
so I thought you should hear
directly from me.

117
00:06:25.263 --> 00:06:29.200
Everything that I do.
I do for you.

118
00:06:29.233 --> 00:06:30.601
I can't sit here
and watch you exist

119
00:06:30.635 --> 00:06:34.404
in a state of sleep paralysis
anymore.

120
00:06:34.437 --> 00:06:37.074
The truth is this:

121
00:06:37.108 --> 00:06:39.476
You are all being used.

122
00:06:39.510 --> 00:06:42.880
You are all
nothing but playthings.

123
00:06:42.914 --> 00:06:44.749
Every soldier
who's gone off to war

124
00:06:44.782 --> 00:06:48.819
thinking that their death
was for an idea.

125
00:06:48.853 --> 00:06:53.324
or that their sacrifice
was important for society.

126
00:06:53.357 --> 00:06:54.926
has been played.

127
00:06:56.527 --> 00:06:59.964
Clinton. Biden. Trump.

128
00:06:59.997 --> 00:07:01.431
You never see them
on the front lines

129
00:07:01.464 --> 00:07:03.134
of any battle.

130
00:07:03.167 --> 00:07:04.735
Why?

131
00:07:04.769 --> 00:07:07.538
Because they'd never
risk their own lives.

132
00:07:07.571 --> 00:07:10.341
They have you.

133
00:07:10.374 --> 00:07:11.842
They have tricked you
into thinking

134
00:07:11.876 --> 00:07:15.646
that you are dying
for your country.

135
00:07:15.680 --> 00:07:19.684
but your country doesn't do
anything for you either.

136
00:07:19.717 --> 00:07:20.785
You walk down the street.

137
00:07:20.818 --> 00:07:25.455
and you get stabbed.
or robbed. killed.

138
00:07:25.488 --> 00:07:28.125
and what does your country do?

139
00:07:28.159 --> 00:07:29.492
Nothing.

140
00:07:30.561 --> 00:07:33.431
And what do you do?

141
00:07:33.463 --> 00:07:35.465
Nothing.

142
00:07:37.101 --> 00:07:39.603
The universe demands balance.

143
00:07:39.637 --> 00:07:42.472
Yin must match yang.

144
00:07:42.506 --> 00:07:44.709
(panting. metal clanking)

145
00:08:24.215 --> 00:08:25.216
Okay.

146
00:08:27.084 --> 00:08:28.753
Listen.

147
00:08:28.786 --> 00:08:31.022
You two don't say anything
when we are in.

148
00:08:31.055 --> 00:08:33.157
I do the talking shit
and you just look angry.

149
00:08:33.190 --> 00:08:34.458
and that's it.

150
00:08:34.492 --> 00:08:36.827
And if that motherfucker's
not paying up today.

151
00:08:36.861 --> 00:08:38.229
you will burn
his fucking store down.

152
00:08:38.262 --> 00:08:39.063
understand?

153
00:08:39.096 --> 00:08:40.765
-Yeah.
-Yes. boss.

154
00:08:40.798 --> 00:08:41.766
Go.

155
00:08:41.799 --> 00:08:44.135
'Cause if you do nothing...

156
00:08:44.168 --> 00:08:46.370
(clicking)

157
00:08:46.404 --> 00:08:48.172
...I have to do something.

158
00:08:48.205 --> 00:08:51.709
(dark music)

159
00:08:51.742 --> 00:08:54.845
I have to do something--
something--do something...

160
00:08:54.879 --> 00:08:56.113
(audio skips. stops abruptly)

161
00:09:10.428 --> 00:09:12.630
What happened to the lights?

162
00:09:13.364 --> 00:09:15.599
(clicking)

163
00:09:15.633 --> 00:09:16.901
(gunfire)

164
00:09:16.934 --> 00:09:18.436
Oh. shit!

165
00:09:18.469 --> 00:09:20.738
(yelps and cries)

166
00:09:20.771 --> 00:09:22.973
(bullet casings
clinking to floor)

167
00:09:26.644 --> 00:09:28.879
(tense music)

168
00:09:45.262 --> 00:09:49.400
Look. This guy is...

169
00:09:49.433 --> 00:09:50.601
greatness. okay?

170
00:09:50.634 --> 00:09:53.137
We need more guys like this
in Canada. okay?

171
00:09:53.170 --> 00:09:54.371
We need 'em!

172
00:09:55.973 --> 00:09:57.308
I love him.

173
00:10:00.244 --> 00:10:01.612
Is that weird?

174
00:10:02.581 --> 00:10:03.881
(click. chime)

175
00:10:05.517 --> 00:10:06.717
(door slams shut)

176
00:10:08.252 --> 00:10:11.355
In an effort to address
these escalating incidents.

177
00:10:11.388 --> 00:10:12.823
we obtained
an official statement

178
00:10:12.857 --> 00:10:15.192
from Interpol
Regional Chief Henry.

179
00:10:15.226 --> 00:10:19.063
who is leading the initiative
to apprehend this vigilante.

180
00:10:21.398 --> 00:10:22.766
Am I reading this one?

181
00:10:22.800 --> 00:10:24.335
Yeah. read it all.

182
00:10:24.368 --> 00:10:26.370
(police radio chatter)

183
00:10:28.607 --> 00:10:30.341
Okay. 203.

184
00:10:30.374 --> 00:10:32.009
1124 here.

185
00:10:32.042 --> 00:10:34.546
Uh. we've calculated
we might need another vehicle.

186
00:10:34.579 --> 00:10:36.113
(staticky blips)

187
00:10:36.147 --> 00:10:37.381
I am here to support

188
00:10:37.414 --> 00:10:39.283
local and federal
law enforcement.

189
00:10:39.316 --> 00:10:42.587
The investigation
is leading to the possibility

190
00:10:42.621 --> 00:10:45.189
of. uh.
international terror cell

191
00:10:45.222 --> 00:10:47.024
that is against democracy.

192
00:10:47.057 --> 00:10:49.994
And it is not impossible
that this terror group

193
00:10:50.027 --> 00:10:55.900
is. uh. a movement supported
by Russian and/or Chinese

194
00:10:55.933 --> 00:10:59.270
government institutions
that. uh.

195
00:10:59.303 --> 00:11:00.505
are not only active online.

196
00:11:00.539 --> 00:11:02.940
but already active
on the ground.

197
00:11:02.973 --> 00:11:06.744
fighting our countries
in the EU and the USA.

198
00:11:06.777 --> 00:11:09.614
There are indications
leading in this direction.

199
00:11:09.648 --> 00:11:11.849
(dark music)

200
00:11:28.966 --> 00:11:31.168
(bus's motor rumbles)

201
00:11:47.284 --> 00:11:49.286
(engine idling)

202
00:11:50.689 --> 00:11:51.623
Hey. hey. hey!

203
00:11:51.656 --> 00:11:53.525
Hey. guys. your tickets.

204
00:11:53.558 --> 00:11:55.292
Fuck you!

205
00:11:56.561 --> 00:11:58.062
Guys.

206
00:12:00.231 --> 00:12:01.899
Guys. you did not pay
your tickets.

207
00:12:01.932 --> 00:12:03.500
It's 1.50 per person.

208
00:12:03.535 --> 00:12:05.369
Fuck off and drive.

209
00:12:05.402 --> 00:12:07.004
It's 1.50 per person.

210
00:12:07.037 --> 00:12:10.274
Didn't I tell you to sit down
and drive the fucking bus?

211
00:12:13.545 --> 00:12:16.247
One-fifty per person. please.

212
00:12:16.280 --> 00:12:17.716
Gentlemen.

213
00:12:17.748 --> 00:12:19.517
Everyone on this bus has
somewhere they have to be.

214
00:12:19.551 --> 00:12:20.652
and for some of us.
it's urgent.

215
00:12:20.685 --> 00:12:22.721
so. please resolve your issues

216
00:12:22.753 --> 00:12:24.288
and go drive the bus.

217
00:12:24.321 --> 00:12:25.489
Which I understand.

218
00:12:25.523 --> 00:12:26.824
It's just the thing

219
00:12:26.857 --> 00:12:27.992
that I will not continue
driving the bus

220
00:12:28.025 --> 00:12:31.028
without everyone having
tickets on it.

221
00:12:37.101 --> 00:12:38.102
Fine.

222
00:12:44.108 --> 00:12:46.810
One-fifty times three.
four-fifty. there you go.

223
00:12:46.844 --> 00:12:48.045
Let me get you your change.

224
00:12:48.078 --> 00:12:50.180
-Keep the change.
-Thank you very much.

225
00:12:50.214 --> 00:12:52.483
-Enjoy.
-What a fuckin' loser.

226
00:12:57.622 --> 00:12:59.423
Thank you.

227
00:13:02.860 --> 00:13:04.962
Who we are
and what we do

228
00:13:04.995 --> 00:13:07.798
has ramifications
in our lives.

229
00:13:07.831 --> 00:13:11.536
and in the lives
of everyone around us. hm?

230
00:13:12.737 --> 00:13:15.172
You don't understand?

231
00:13:15.205 --> 00:13:18.342
All right. Pay attention.
let me explain this to you.

232
00:13:18.375 --> 00:13:19.243
If you get onto a bus

233
00:13:19.276 --> 00:13:21.178
and you don't pay
your ticket.

234
00:13:21.211 --> 00:13:22.614
if you go to the movie theater.

235
00:13:22.647 --> 00:13:24.848
if you grab a banana
at a grocery store

236
00:13:24.882 --> 00:13:26.450
and you don't pay.

237
00:13:26.483 --> 00:13:29.987
eventually. the cost
of everything will go up.

238
00:13:30.020 --> 00:13:31.889
If ten percent doesn't pay.

239
00:13:31.922 --> 00:13:35.326
the cost will go up ten percent
to cover the loss.

240
00:13:35.359 --> 00:13:37.328
and that's not fair.

241
00:13:39.863 --> 00:13:41.666
You might not understand this.

242
00:13:41.700 --> 00:13:43.434
but think about it.

243
00:13:43.467 --> 00:13:46.170
I'm sure you'll come
to the right decision.

244
00:13:49.940 --> 00:13:52.610
(dark music)

245
00:13:52.644 --> 00:13:54.244
You're gonna look back
at this moment

246
00:13:54.278 --> 00:13:59.350
and realize that it is
the luckiest you have ever been.

247
00:13:59.383 --> 00:14:01.285
Believe me.

248
00:14:17.901 --> 00:14:20.137
(metallic rattling)

249
00:14:32.316 --> 00:14:33.350
(gun cocking)

250
00:14:53.805 --> 00:14:56.006
(brakes hissing)

251
00:14:56.039 --> 00:14:58.510
Thanks for the tickets. sir.

252
00:15:02.112 --> 00:15:04.348
(engine rumbling)

253
00:15:10.921 --> 00:15:13.157
(faint whooshing of traffic)

254
00:15:21.900 --> 00:15:24.168
(birds chirping)

255
00:15:33.611 --> 00:15:35.680
(indistinct chatter)

256
00:15:42.754 --> 00:15:45.022
(machinery beeping)

257
00:15:54.064 --> 00:15:56.333
(whimpering)

258
00:16:01.606 --> 00:16:02.640
(chair clanking)

259
00:16:25.964 --> 00:16:26.931
Please. only ten minutes.

260
00:16:26.965 --> 00:16:28.633
She's very weak.

261
00:16:37.074 --> 00:16:39.076
Hello. Elsa.

262
00:16:42.514 --> 00:16:44.348
(faint exclamation)

263
00:16:44.381 --> 00:16:47.351
I can't even imagine
everything you've been through.

264
00:16:50.522 --> 00:16:52.857
What do you want?

265
00:16:52.891 --> 00:16:55.259
Who are you?

266
00:16:55.292 --> 00:16:58.195
I'm just here to help.

267
00:16:58.228 --> 00:17:01.633
What do you want to happen?

268
00:17:01.666 --> 00:17:03.200
What do you mean?

269
00:17:03.233 --> 00:17:05.803
The men who did this to you.

270
00:17:05.837 --> 00:17:10.040
What do you want
to happen to them?

271
00:17:10.073 --> 00:17:12.911
I want them

272
00:17:12.944 --> 00:17:15.345
to go to jail

273
00:17:15.379 --> 00:17:18.783
for the rest of their lives.

274
00:17:21.019 --> 00:17:22.219
Hm.

275
00:17:23.755 --> 00:17:25.590
And they might.

276
00:17:26.791 --> 00:17:30.193
Of course. we won't know
