00:37:07.171 --> 00:37:10.675
Unfortunately.
it seems like a coincidence.

545
00:37:10.708 --> 00:37:13.177
I do go to that bar
quite often.

546
00:37:13.211 --> 00:37:14.846
It's one of my favorite bars.

547
00:37:14.879 --> 00:37:17.380
Could I have been at the bar

548
00:37:17.414 --> 00:37:21.318
and moved a glass from a stool
where I wanted to sit?

549
00:37:21.351 --> 00:37:23.855
Potentially.
It's definitely a possibility.

550
00:37:23.888 --> 00:37:24.856
(energetic music)

551
00:37:24.889 --> 00:37:26.023
Hey!

552
00:37:26.057 --> 00:37:28.492
-What is wrong with you?
-Dude. my head is spinning.

553
00:37:28.526 --> 00:37:30.094
Are you--Do you want--
D-Do--

554
00:37:30.128 --> 00:37:32.029
-Uh. are you okay?
-Come on. rich boy.

555
00:37:32.063 --> 00:37:35.933
(indistinct)

556
00:37:35.967 --> 00:37:37.869
I think he's playing with us.

557
00:37:39.469 --> 00:37:40.538
-Are you--
-I'm good. I'm good.

558
00:37:40.571 --> 00:37:41.873
Give me a second.
give me a second.

559
00:37:41.906 --> 00:37:43.674
Can you answer something?

560
00:37:46.210 --> 00:37:48.478
Okay. What's wrong? Come on.

561
00:37:48.513 --> 00:37:50.248
Do you need some water.
or do you want to. like--

562
00:37:50.280 --> 00:37:52.650
(voice trails off)

563
00:37:52.683 --> 00:37:55.119
I think it's time
for you girls to go.

564
00:37:55.153 --> 00:37:56.721
-Why?
-What do you mean?

565
00:37:56.754 --> 00:37:58.388
These two guys.
when you were in the bathroom.

566
00:37:58.421 --> 00:37:59.791
they put something
in your drink.

567
00:37:59.824 --> 00:38:01.058
-Are you serious?
-What are you talking about?

568
00:38:01.092 --> 00:38:02.760
I switched them.
That's what's going on.

569
00:38:02.794 --> 00:38:04.729
They drank 'em. Hence...

570
00:38:04.762 --> 00:38:05.395
(slaps)

571
00:38:05.428 --> 00:38:06.731
...sleepy-time.

572
00:38:06.764 --> 00:38:10.568
So. no matter what you do.
you don't have to go home.

573
00:38:10.601 --> 00:38:12.770
but I wouldn't stay with them.

574
00:38:12.804 --> 00:38:13.604
Have a good night.

575
00:38:13.638 --> 00:38:14.772
Ugh. fuck.

576
00:38:16.373 --> 00:38:19.076
-Let's just go.
-Fucking bullshit.

577
00:38:19.110 --> 00:38:21.444
(concerned murmuring)

578
00:39:12.763 --> 00:39:14.397
We sure this is the right house?

579
00:39:14.431 --> 00:39:16.701
It's what I was told.

580
00:39:16.734 --> 00:39:17.568
We're ready.

581
00:39:17.602 --> 00:39:18.269
Good.

582
00:39:18.302 --> 00:39:19.270
Let's move.

583
00:39:19.303 --> 00:39:21.973
(dramatic music)

584
00:39:57.541 --> 00:39:59.777
(chains clinking)

585
00:39:59.810 --> 00:40:01.712
(saw cutting)

586
00:40:03.614 --> 00:40:05.950
(chains clattering)

587
00:40:13.958 --> 00:40:14.892
Guns up!

588
00:40:29.472 --> 00:40:31.042
Go. go. go. go.

589
00:40:45.289 --> 00:40:48.458
(gun clicking)

590
00:41:43.848 --> 00:41:45.049
(clicking)

591
00:41:48.319 --> 00:41:49.153
(device beeps)

592
00:41:49.186 --> 00:41:50.254
(fire swooshes)

593
00:41:51.222 --> 00:41:52.857
(door bangs)

594
00:42:03.134 --> 00:42:05.069
(overlapping chatter)

595
00:42:05.102 --> 00:42:07.705
(news fanfare)

596
00:42:07.738 --> 00:42:10.775
It's possible that this
is not just a single individual.

597
00:42:10.808 --> 00:42:13.844
However. what remains clear
is that our current system

598
00:42:13.878 --> 00:42:16.580
is failing
to protect our citizens.

599
00:42:16.614 --> 00:42:19.350
This raises critical questions.

600
00:42:19.383 --> 00:42:21.752
If the risks associated
with migration

601
00:42:21.786 --> 00:42:23.621
outweigh the benefits.

602
00:42:23.654 --> 00:42:26.690
and if migrants are contributing
more to societal cost

603
00:42:26.724 --> 00:42:28.426
than economic gains.

604
00:42:28.459 --> 00:42:30.661
then it may be time
to reevaluate

605
00:42:30.694 --> 00:42:32.563
our migration policies.

606
00:42:32.596 --> 00:42:35.699
(tense music)

607
00:43:02.827 --> 00:43:05.663
Three. two. one. Go.

608
00:43:05.696 --> 00:43:06.430
(device beeps)

609
00:43:06.464 --> 00:43:08.065
(explosion)

610
00:43:08.099 --> 00:43:09.700
(heavy bang)

611
00:43:11.368 --> 00:43:14.305
(smoke bomb clattering)

612
00:43:14.338 --> 00:43:17.308
(smoke bomb booming)

613
00:43:26.518 --> 00:43:27.418
Come out.

614
00:43:27.451 --> 00:43:28.652
Surrender.

615
00:43:28.686 --> 00:43:31.689
I understand that you're here
to do your job.

616
00:43:31.722 --> 00:43:33.657
I have no interest
in killing all of you.

617
00:43:33.691 --> 00:43:36.327
but if you try to stop me
from doing my job.

618
00:43:36.360 --> 00:43:39.130
I will be forced
to kill you all.

619
00:43:39.163 --> 00:43:41.866
This is your last warning
to leave.

620
00:43:43.167 --> 00:43:43.968
Fire!

621
00:43:44.001 --> 00:43:45.604
(guns firing)

622
00:43:45.636 --> 00:43:48.239
(upbeat music)

623
00:43:53.310 --> 00:43:54.345
(guns firing)

624
00:43:54.378 --> 00:43:56.914
(screams)

625
00:43:59.183 --> 00:44:01.385
(impact sounds)

626
00:44:11.630 --> 00:44:13.931
Team B. you're on. Let's go.

627
00:44:15.299 --> 00:44:16.535
(grunts of pain)

628
00:44:16.568 --> 00:44:18.435
(yells)

629
00:44:18.469 --> 00:44:20.404
Let's move. move. move. move.

630
00:44:21.739 --> 00:44:24.341
(pained yells)

631
00:44:27.311 --> 00:44:29.747
(screams)

632
00:44:32.049 --> 00:44:33.384
(blood sprays)

633
00:44:34.251 --> 00:44:36.153
(shrieks)

634
00:44:38.489 --> 00:44:40.057
(groans)

635
00:44:44.161 --> 00:44:46.697
(shrieks)

636
00:44:56.840 --> 00:44:59.644
(glass shatters)

637
00:44:59.678 --> 00:45:01.979
(blood gushing)

638
00:45:04.649 --> 00:45:07.851
(distant yelling)

639
00:45:22.466 --> 00:45:25.436
(indistinct office chatter)

640
00:45:29.940 --> 00:45:31.875
What's the matter?

641
00:45:33.177 --> 00:45:34.945
Mr. Sanders.

642
00:45:34.979 --> 00:45:37.047
We had no idea
you were dropping by today.

643
00:45:37.081 --> 00:45:38.683
Well. it wouldn't be much
of a surprise inspection

644
00:45:38.717 --> 00:45:40.217
if you did. would it?

645
00:45:40.251 --> 00:45:42.721
Well. we do have the half-year
figures for you. so--

646
00:45:42.753 --> 00:45:44.822
-Good.
-Please. follow me to my--

647
00:45:44.855 --> 00:45:46.457
To your office.

648
00:45:46.490 --> 00:45:48.959
(keyboard clacking)

649
00:45:53.632 --> 00:45:56.066
(sighs)

650
00:46:00.871 --> 00:46:01.905
Uh. hope you don't mind me

651
00:46:01.939 --> 00:46:03.240
using your office
while you're gone.

652
00:46:03.274 --> 00:46:06.076
Gonna need some privacy
for delicate calls with tenants

653
00:46:06.110 --> 00:46:07.679
who are behind on their rent.

654
00:46:07.712 --> 00:46:08.879
How many are behind on the rent?

655
00:46:08.912 --> 00:46:10.515
Oh. we're always under 10%.

656
00:46:10.548 --> 00:46:14.552
So. on average. 90% of the rent
comes in each month.

657
00:46:14.586 --> 00:46:15.587
Are there fluctuations.

658
00:46:15.620 --> 00:46:17.488
or is it the same 10%
each month?

659
00:46:17.522 --> 00:46:19.658
If so. I want them evicted.

660
00:46:19.691 --> 00:46:22.393
Well. the procedure is after
three months of unpaid rent.

661
00:46:22.426 --> 00:46:25.296
we send a final notice
to pay within four weeks.

662
00:46:25.329 --> 00:46:27.398
And if that payment
doesn't come through.

663
00:46:27.431 --> 00:46:28.566
we get a court order.

664
00:46:28.600 --> 00:46:30.702
And that will allow us
to evict them

665
00:46:30.735 --> 00:46:32.469
within seven months total.

666
00:46:33.804 --> 00:46:34.972
So. if somebody
doesn't want to pay.

667
00:46:35.005 --> 00:46:37.474
they get to live for free
for seven months.

668
00:46:38.976 --> 00:46:41.111
If you want to see it that way.
then you're right.

669
00:46:41.145 --> 00:46:42.980
Is there another way
to look at it?

670
00:46:43.013 --> 00:46:45.082
We have 3.500 units
in this city. Owen.

671
00:46:45.115 --> 00:46:48.586
That brings us in
50.400.000 Euro annually.

672
00:46:48.620 --> 00:46:50.988
10% of that
is 5.040.000 Euros

673
00:46:51.021 --> 00:46:54.058
that people
are stealing from me.

674
00:46:55.392 --> 00:46:56.695
That's unacceptable.

675
00:46:56.728 --> 00:46:58.596
Evict them immediately.

676
00:46:58.630 --> 00:47:00.964
Well. the problem is the courts
won't order an eviction

677
00:47:00.998 --> 00:47:03.300
anytime sooner than that.

678
00:47:03.334 --> 00:47:05.369
May be true.

679
00:47:05.402 --> 00:47:08.238
So. you'll start pressuring them
after four weeks of nonpayment.

680
00:47:08.272 --> 00:47:10.107
If that doesn't work.
you give me their addresses

681
00:47:10.140 --> 00:47:12.276
and my people will sort it out.

682
00:47:12.309 --> 00:47:14.078
Okay. um...

683
00:47:15.513 --> 00:47:17.348
...we can try that.

684
00:47:17.381 --> 00:47:19.283
No. We do that.

685
00:47:20.317 --> 00:47:22.419
How's the Grand Allee project
coming along?

686
00:47:23.621 --> 00:47:25.189
Um. technical acceptance

687
00:47:25.222 --> 00:47:26.825
is scheduled
for the end of the week.

688
00:47:26.857 --> 00:47:30.127
So. all tenants
can move back in on Monday.

689
00:47:31.596 --> 00:47:33.364
What a shitshow that was.

690
00:47:33.397 --> 00:47:35.165
We're never using
that contractor again.

691
00:47:35.199 --> 00:47:36.634
No.

692
00:47:36.668 --> 00:47:40.237
Also. Owen. the plumbing
in my villa's not finished yet.

693
00:47:40.938 --> 00:47:43.240
-Have them get on that.
-Sure.

694
00:47:43.273 --> 00:47:46.745
Also. went by
the Ljubljana project.

695
00:47:46.778 --> 00:47:48.513
I took some pictures.

696
00:47:48.546 --> 00:47:49.880
Look at this.

697
00:47:51.516 --> 00:47:53.518
Oh. That's bad.

698
00:47:53.551 --> 00:47:55.986
Uh. I mean.
the gauge will be an easy fix.

699
00:47:56.019 --> 00:47:57.789
but the facade--

700
00:47:57.822 --> 00:47:59.524
No.

701
00:47:59.557 --> 00:48:02.126
No. we don't do a project
that big on that building.

702
00:48:02.159 --> 00:48:04.395
Just make sure it's not
gonna collapse.

703
00:48:05.797 --> 00:48:07.398
Certainly.

704
00:48:10.067 --> 00:48:14.104
Huh. well. we sure miss
having your father around here.

705
00:48:14.138 --> 00:48:15.139
Hm.

706
00:48:16.306 --> 00:48:19.109
Never went hunting with my dad.

707
00:48:19.143 --> 00:48:20.678
No?

708
00:48:20.712 --> 00:48:22.580
-Hm. that's surprising.
-Is it?

709
00:48:23.715 --> 00:48:24.915
My mother died when I was young

710
00:48:24.948 --> 00:48:27.418
and he just shipped me off
to boarding school.

711
00:48:28.620 --> 00:48:30.387
I saw him two times a year.

712
00:48:31.556 --> 00:48:33.157
I don't know anything about him.

713
00:48:33.190 --> 00:48:35.058
Didn't even know he had cancer.

714
00:48:35.092 --> 00:48:37.227
I'm sorry to hear that.

715
00:48:40.264 --> 00:48:42.299
Oh. he always was very proud

716
00:48:42.332 --> 00:48:44.636
of your career in the military.
though.

717
00:48:54.512 --> 00:48:56.781
Sort out that 10%. Owen.

718
00:48:56.815 --> 00:48:58.015
Understood.

719
00:48:58.949 --> 00:49:01.920
Uh. there is one more issue
to address.

720
00:49:01.952 --> 00:49:03.987
Uh. recently.
the tax authorities

721
00:49:04.021 --> 00:49:05.389
investigated deeper
into the ownership

722
00:49:05.422 --> 00:49:08.959
of your holding companies.
and that raised a few questions.

723
00:49:08.992 --> 00:49:11.830
I mean. since you're not
a registered citizen here.

724
00:49:11.863 --> 00:49:14.164
nor did you enter
the country legally.

725
00:49:14.198 --> 00:49:18.202
uh. we might run
in a few problems.

726
00:49:19.002 --> 00:49:20.505
We own a lot
of social housing units.

727
00:49:20.538 --> 00:49:23.641
and. uh. the government
wants to seize empty units

728
00:49:23.675 --> 00:49:25.543
for housing migrants.

729
00:49:25.577 --> 00:49:26.477
No.

730
00:49:26.511 --> 00:49:30.013
We can rent them to them
at full cost.

731
00:49:30.815 --> 00:49:32.684
What do we always say. Owen?

732
00:49:34.017 --> 00:49:35.620
No empty units.

733
00:49:35.653 --> 00:49:36.921
No empty units.

734
00:49:36.955 --> 00:49:39.591
They want to know
who owns those companies.

735
00:49:39.624 --> 00:49:42.292
And if we fail
to provide that information.

736
00:49:42.326 --> 00:49:44.929
they will seize all the units
on the Kazin block.

737
00:49:44.963 --> 00:49:46.731
without payment or revenue.

738
00:49:46.764 --> 00:49:47.832
Well. I'm sure our lawyers

739
00:49:47.866 --> 00:49:49.767
will have something to say
about that.

740
00:49:49.801 --> 00:49:50.869
Certainly.

741
00:49:50.902 --> 00:49:53.470
But there is only so much
they can do.

742
00:49:55.072 --> 00:49:56.373
I urge you to reconsider

743
00:49:56.406 --> 00:49:59.443
and provide the information
they requested.

744
00:49:59.476 --> 00:50:00.712
Leave.

745
00:50:00.745 --> 00:50:03.313
After all. they will probably
roll out the red carpet for you

746
00:50:03.347 --> 00:50:07.150
and even grant you citizenship
without asking any question.

747
00:50:07.184 --> 00:50:09.319
Oh. I'm an American. Owen.

748
00:50:09.353 --> 00:50:12.356
I'm just here
on an extended vacation.

749
00:50:16.895 --> 00:50:18.663
-Sort the 10%.
-Yes. sir.

750
00:50:18.696 --> 00:50:22.366
Oh. uh. and here are
the half-year figures for you.

751
00:50:23.768 --> 00:50:25.435
I've seen 'em.

752
00:50:32.777 --> 00:50:34.378
(sighs)

753
00:50:34.411 --> 00:50:36.346
(typing)

754
00:50:43.053 --> 00:50:45.489
It smells like a nursing home
in here.

755
00:50:47.324 --> 00:50:49.359
Let's get some fresh blood.

756
00:50:51.495 --> 00:50:52.664
(door slams)

757
00:50:52.697 --> 00:50:55.533
(suspenseful music)

758
00:51:02.040 --> 00:51:04.374
(metal clinking)

759
00:51:06.476 --> 00:51:08.345
(knife swishing)

760
00:51:15.218 --> 00:51:18.388
(traffic sounds)

761
00:51:22.961 --> 00:51:25.663
(glasses clinking)

762
00:51:33.571 --> 00:51:35.039
So early?

763
00:51:35.073 --> 00:51:37.542
It's been a long day. Jenny.

764
00:51:38.108 --> 00:51:40.511
Huh. Okay.

765
00:51:47.284 --> 00:51:48.720
(liquid sloshing)

766
00:51:48.753 --> 00:51:50.487
Uh. here.

767
00:51:56.393 --> 00:51:59.597
Okay. I go back.
I have a delivery.

768
00:51:59.631 --> 00:52:01.733
Ah. I'll watch the bar.

769
00:52:01.766 --> 00:52:03.735
Yes. Okay.

770
00:52:13.243 --> 00:52:17.915
Well. my father
and I were estranged.

771
00:52:17.949 --> 00:52:19.216
I guess you could say.

772
00:52:19.249 --> 00:52:22.854
Um. I didn't really have
much of a relationship

773
00:52:22.887 --> 00:52:25.222
with him growing up.

774
00:52:25.255 --> 00:52:28.026
Uh. my mother passed
when I was young.

775
00:52:28.059 --> 00:52:31.729
And I think
the emotional weight

776
00:52:31.763 --> 00:52:32.897
of my mother's passing.

777
00:52:32.930 --> 00:52:36.433
as well as the weight
of trying to grow his company

778
00:52:36.466 --> 00:52:40.203
meant that he had
other priorities.

779
00:52:40.237 --> 00:52:42.305
which is something
I've come to terms with.

780
00:52:42.339 --> 00:52:45.943
And now that
I'm running things around here.

781
00:52:45.977 --> 00:52:47.444
I can really understand.

782
00:52:47.477 --> 00:52:50.548
So. it's not like
I hold it against him anymore.

783
00:52:50.581 --> 00:52:54.619
I was still in active duty
in the United States Army.

784
00:52:54.652 --> 00:52:58.388
And we got a call in the office
that I was working in

785
00:52:58.422 --> 00:53:00.558
letting me know
that my father had passed.

786
00:53:00.591 --> 00:53:05.029
I found myself on my way here
for the first time...

787
00:53:05.063 --> 00:53:08.533
couple days later
for his funeral.

788
00:53:08.566 --> 00:53:10.233
(sirens)

789
00:53:10.267 --> 00:53:12.904
(ominous music)

790
00:53:12.937 --> 00:53:16.239
(walkie-talkie chatter)

791
00:53:21.278 --> 00:53:24.381
(footsteps approaching)

792
00:53:45.235 --> 00:53:47.872
Oh. What a fucking mess.

793
00:53:50.975 --> 00:53:52.643
He's playing with us.

794
00:53:55.580 --> 00:53:57.782
There's nobody
in that box anymore.

795
00:53:59.016 --> 00:54:00.685
Check the perimeter.

796
00:54:01.919 --> 00:54:03.621
Check their pulse.

797
00:54:06.090 --> 00:54:07.792
Fuck!

798
00:54:11.996 --> 00:54:13.598
(tense music)

799
00:54:17.802 --> 00:54:19.637
This shit has to stop.

800
00:54:21.172 --> 00:54:23.007
It's gonna stop.

801
00:54:29.881 --> 00:54:31.516
Good afternoon.

802
00:54:31.549 --> 00:54:34.652
Yes? What do you want?

803
00:54:34.685 --> 00:54:35.953
Who are you?

804
00:54:35.987 --> 00:54:38.355
Another one of those reporters?

805
00:54:38.388 --> 00:54:40.625
Do I look like
a reporter to you?

806
00:54:41.526 --> 00:54:43.694
No. I just have one question.

807
00:54:43.728 --> 00:54:45.263
Were you satisfied
with the result

808
00:54:45.295 --> 00:54:46.931
that was reached in court?

809
00:54:47.832 --> 00:54:49.233
And was your daughter?

810
00:54:49.267 --> 00:54:50.433
Why do you ask this?

811
00:54:50.467 --> 00:54:52.103
How can you ask this?

812
00:54:52.136 --> 00:54:54.272
How do you know where we live?

813
00:54:54.304 --> 00:54:59.342
So. you found no justice
in court. right?

814
00:54:59.376 --> 00:55:01.879
I don't have to answer
your questions. man.

815
00:55:01.913 --> 00:55:03.548
This is bullshit. Go away.

816
00:55:03.581 --> 00:55:04.849
No.

817
00:55:07.285 --> 00:55:09.787
There was no justice.

818
00:55:16.828 --> 00:55:18.663
Have a good afternoon.

819
00:55:23.333 --> 00:55:25.670
(sighs)

820
00:55:31.075 --> 00:55:34.045
(machines beeping)

821
00:55:39.416 --> 00:55:42.086
Hello. Elsa.

822
00:55:42.119 --> 00:55:44.088
I'm with Interpol.

823
00:55:44.121 --> 00:55:47.325
And we are very sorry
with what happened to you.

824
00:55:47.390 --> 00:55:49.727
Please believe me.

825
00:55:49.760 --> 00:55:53.798
We will use all of our resources
to find whoever did this to you.

826
00:55:53.831 --> 00:55:56.366
and put them in jail
for a long time.

827
00:55:56.399 --> 00:55:59.402
But you told me
that you have them.

828
00:55:59.436 --> 00:56:01.672
that you know where they are.

829
00:56:01.706 --> 00:56:04.508
Elsa.
I have not been here before.

830
00:56:04.542 --> 00:56:06.844
This is the first time
we're talking.

831
00:56:07.712 --> 00:56:09.046
Y-You were in a coma
for three weeks.

832
00:56:09.080 --> 00:56:11.949
You maybe. you mistaken me
with somebody else.

833
00:56:11.983 --> 00:56:14.118
(rasped breathing)

834
00:56:16.220 --> 00:56:21.092
Yes. Maybe it was your colleague
that...

835
00:56:23.361 --> 00:56:25.796
He was very friendly.

836
00:56:27.565 --> 00:56:30.902
He asked me if I want justice.

837
00:56:31.903 --> 00:56:33.436
My colleague?

838
00:56:34.705 --> 00:56:36.107
Was he wearing a uniform?

839
00:56:36.140 --> 00:56:38.009
Did he give you a name?

840
00:56:40.111 --> 00:56:40.912
(groans)

841
00:56:40.945 --> 00:56:42.412
What did he look like?

842
00:56:43.413 --> 00:56:44.782
What did he look like?

843
00:56:44.815 --> 00:56:46.517
He was small.

844
00:56:48.386 --> 00:56:49.486
Caucasian?

845
00:56:49.520 --> 00:56:54.457
No. More Middle-Eastern looking.

846
00:56:55.492 --> 00:56:57.962
Uh. black hair.

847
00:56:59.363 --> 00:57:00.765
Beard.

848
00:57:01.966 --> 00:57:06.504
Elsa. would it be okay if I get
our sketch-artist to come

849
00:57:06.537 --> 00:57:08.072
so you can give a description?

850
00:57:08.105 --> 00:57:10.141
Then it would be a great help.

851
00:57:11.842 --> 00:57:12.977
You rest. okay?

852
00:57:13.010 --> 00:57:14.111
Mm.

853
00:57:15.513 --> 00:57:17.048
I will come back.

854
00:57:18.349 --> 00:57:20.184
(machines beeping)

855
00:57:22.520 --> 00:57:24.088
Rest a while.

856
00:57:31.128 --> 00:57:33.064
(door creaks)

857
00:57:33.097 --> 00:57:35.800
(dark music)

858
00:57:41.605 --> 00:57:44.008
(footsteps approaching)

859
00:58:02.660 --> 00:58:04.328
(non-English taunting)

860
00:58:04.362 --> 00:58:05.495
I-I don't understand you.

861
00:58:05.529 --> 00:58:07.531
(overlapping taunts)

862
00:58:08.933 --> 00:58:10.534
Please. just.
can I please just have--

863
00:58:10.568 --> 00:58:12.670
(overlapping taunts)

864
00:58:14.238 --> 00:58:16.007
No. no!

865
00:58:16.040 --> 00:58:19.677
No. no. okay. I just--
No. please. no. don't do that.

866
00:58:19.710 --> 00:58:21.545
(overlapping taunts)

867
00:58:21.579 --> 00:58:24.181
(suspenseful music)

868
00:58:36.394 --> 00:58:38.963
(distant commotion)

869
00:58:38.996 --> 00:58:39.930
Please. just--

870
00:58:39.964 --> 00:58:41.732
(pained grunts)

871
00:58:44.068 --> 00:58:45.102
-You want?
-Please.

872
00:58:45.136 --> 00:58:45.936
Your telephone. huh?

873
00:58:45.970 --> 00:58:46.871
Call your mommy.

874
00:58:46.904 --> 00:58:48.739
(pained groans)

875
00:58:48.773 --> 00:58:49.840
(mean laughter. camera snaps)

876
00:58:49.874 --> 00:58:51.642
(harsh slap)

877
00:58:53.377 --> 00:58:55.279
(non-English taunting)

878
00:58:55.312 --> 00:58:57.448
(grunts)

879
00:58:57.481 --> 00:59:00.951
I just need my--I just need
my phone. that's...that's all.

880
00:59:00.985 --> 00:59:01.752
That's all.

881
00:59:01.786 --> 00:59:03.487
(grunts)

882
00:59:03.522 --> 00:59:06.257
(indistinct taunting)

883
00:59:06.290 --> 00:59:07.158
(Taser buzzing)

884
00:59:07.191 --> 00:59:08.359
(shrieks)

885
00:59:08.392 --> 00:59:10.094
(yells)

886
00:59:12.096 --> 00:59:13.297
-Ugh.
-Get your phone.

887
00:59:13.330 --> 00:59:14.465
Call your parents.

888
00:59:14.498 --> 00:59:15.534
Just tell them
you want to press charges

889
00:59:15.566 --> 00:59:17.468
on each one of these
pieces of shit.

890
00:59:17.501 --> 00:59:19.570
I'll give you their names.

891
00:59:22.039 --> 00:59:24.543
(pained moan)

892
00:59:24.575 --> 00:59:26.043
Hello. boys.

893
00:59:26.077 --> 00:59:27.711
You remember me?

894
00:59:29.880 --> 00:59:32.750
If I ever see you put your hands
on anyone else ever again.

895
00:59:32.783 --> 00:59:34.519
I will visit you.

896
00:59:34.553 --> 00:59:36.087
and you will not be walking away
from it.

897
00:59:36.120 --> 00:59:37.822
You understand?

898
00:59:39.423 --> 00:59:40.624
And you.

899
00:59:41.526 --> 00:59:42.493
You remember when I told you
on the bus

900
00:59:42.527 --> 00:59:44.728
that it was your lucky day?

901
00:59:44.762 --> 00:59:47.064
Maybe now you understand why.

902
00:59:49.333 --> 00:59:50.134
(bones cracking)

903
00:59:50.167 --> 00:59:51.202
(screams)

904
00:59:51.235 --> 00:59:52.103
(bones snapping)

905
00:59:52.136 --> 00:59:53.003
(yells)

906
00:59:53.037 --> 00:59:53.871
(bones crunching)

907
00:59:53.904 --> 00:59:56.040
(groans)

908
00:59:58.510 --> 00:59:59.210
(bones breaking)

909
00:59:59.243 --> 01:00:00.611
(cries out)

910
01:00:01.412 --> 01:00:03.280
(pained moans)

911
01:00:21.198 --> 01:00:23.200
(screaming)

912
01:00:27.905 --> 01:00:30.407
If the police
don't protect you.

913
01:00:30.441 --> 01:00:32.309
I have to protect you.

914
01:00:32.343 --> 01:00:36.413
And if the courts and laws
don't give you justice...

915
01:00:37.582 --> 01:00:40.084
I will give you justice.

916
01:00:40.117 --> 01:00:44.021
And remember.
I do this for you...

917
01:00:45.489 --> 01:00:49.293
until you learn
to do it for yourself.

918
01:00:49.326 --> 01:00:51.328
(tense music)

919
01:00:58.335 --> 01:01:00.337
(camera shutters clicking)

920
01:01:01.438 --> 01:01:03.440
(sirens wailing)

921
01:01:07.378 --> 01:01:08.245
Yes.

922
01:01:12.617 --> 01:01:13.817
Understood.

923
01:01:15.920 --> 01:01:17.556
We searched the neighborhood.

924
01:01:17.589 --> 01:01:19.624
Full lockdown.
two miles perimeter.

925
01:01:19.658 --> 01:01:20.858
Nothing.

926
01:01:21.959 --> 01:01:23.928
This place was rented
under Molly Ling.

927
01:01:23.961 --> 01:01:25.396
a Chinese woman
who was paid cash

928
01:01:25.429 --> 01:01:26.931
to sign the lease.

929
01:01:26.964 --> 01:01:29.466
She said the mechanic
gave her the money

930
01:01:29.500 --> 01:01:31.802
but stated
he had no work permit.

931
01:01:33.538 --> 01:01:34.471
Tell me.

932
01:01:35.339 --> 01:01:37.107
Upstairs all clear.

933
01:01:37.141 --> 01:01:38.275
Look around.

934
01:01:39.176 --> 01:01:40.377
Nothing personal.

935
01:01:41.646 --> 01:01:43.147
This was all a facade...

936
01:01:44.616 --> 01:01:46.183
to set up a fortress.

937
01:01:48.520 --> 01:01:50.120
Open it.

938
01:01:50.154 --> 01:01:51.322
Let's go. move.

939
01:02:02.601 --> 01:02:04.001
Let's go. go. go!

940
01:02:05.502 --> 01:02:07.505
(saw grinding)

941
01:02:27.592 --> 01:02:29.793
(suspenseful music)

942
01:02:36.300 --> 01:02:37.401
Judge Reinhold.

943
01:02:37.434 --> 01:02:38.335
Who are you?

944
01:02:38.369 --> 01:02:39.738
Here from
the Chief Inspector's Office.

945
01:02:39.770 --> 01:02:41.338
We have new information
that's come to light.

946
01:02:57.821 --> 01:02:59.456
(camera beeps. shutter clicks)

947
01:02:59.490 --> 01:03:01.492
(indistinct radio chatter)

948
01:03:47.438 --> 01:03:49.574
Hope you're not feeling
too nauseous. Judge.

949
01:03:50.709 --> 01:03:52.409
That shot I gave you...

950
01:03:53.911 --> 01:03:55.212
it's gonna be very suspicious

951
01:03:55.245 --> 01:03:57.549
when that turns up
in your blood. isn't it?

952
01:03:57.582 --> 01:03:59.651
Let's hope they don't run
a toxicology report

953
01:03:59.684 --> 01:04:01.051
on your body.

954
01:04:03.454 --> 01:04:04.488
Eh. who knows?

955
01:04:04.522 --> 01:04:08.092
Maybe you have a bit
of a tolerance for heroin.

956
01:04:08.125 --> 01:04:10.394
Seem to like heroin dealers.
anyway.

957
01:04:11.495 --> 01:04:14.164
How many of them have you
let back onto the street?

958
01:04:15.966 --> 01:04:20.070
The laws are meant to protect
the victims. right?

959
01:04:20.672 --> 01:04:22.005
It's not the perpetrators.

960
01:04:22.039 --> 01:04:24.542
Maybe that's when you lost
your north star.

961
01:04:24.576 --> 01:04:28.979
when you started using the laws
to help people hurt people.

962
01:04:31.215 --> 01:04:33.384
You know. it's not just
the perpetrators.

963
01:04:33.417 --> 01:04:35.986
You cause collateral damage.
Judge.

964
01:04:36.019 --> 01:04:38.389
It's people like you
letting people get away

965
01:04:38.422 --> 01:04:41.091
with rape and murder.

966
01:04:41.826 --> 01:04:43.862
Excusing their behavior.

967
01:04:43.894 --> 01:04:48.198
Letting people get away
with rape and murder.

968
01:04:48.232 --> 01:04:52.369
Six boys raped
a 14-year-old girl.

969
01:04:52.403 --> 01:04:55.540
I saw your interview
in front of the courthouse.

970
01:04:55.573 --> 01:05:01.579
Saw you say that these boys
just had an adjustment issue.

971
01:05:01.613 --> 01:05:05.583
that they didn't know
how to fit in to society.

972
01:05:06.984 --> 01:05:09.119
But what you don't understand
is the society

973
01:05:09.153 --> 01:05:11.088
that you think
they don't fit into

974
01:05:11.121 --> 01:05:14.659
is falling apart and dying.

975
01:05:15.627 --> 01:05:19.263
And you are the cancer
that is killing it.

976
01:05:22.199 --> 01:05:23.902
And you know. Judge.
it's people like you

977
01:05:23.934 --> 01:05:25.936
letting these people
get away with it...

978
01:05:26.704 --> 01:05:28.439
excusing their behavior.

979
01:05:29.507 --> 01:05:31.975
Hm? How do you think
that makes the families feel?

980
01:05:34.011 --> 01:05:36.213
(saw grinding)

981
01:05:50.961 --> 01:05:52.996
(beeping)

982
01:05:53.030 --> 01:05:54.398
(explosion)

983
01:05:54.431 --> 01:05:55.466
(flames billowing)

984
01:05:55.499 --> 01:05:57.802
(groaning)

985
01:05:57.836 --> 01:06:00.037
(shouting)

986
01:06:14.384 --> 01:06:16.921
(soft music)

987
01:06:16.955 --> 01:06:18.288
(panting)

988
01:06:18.322 --> 01:06:19.056
(man groans)

989
01:06:24.461 --> 01:06:25.597
(coughing)

990
01:06:38.810 --> 01:06:39.611
(sighs)

991
01:06:42.212 --> 01:06:45.517
Human beings are such sheep.

992
01:06:45.550 --> 01:06:47.852
Even when you push them
to the limit.

993
01:06:47.886 --> 01:06:49.554
they will obey the law.

994
01:06:49.587 --> 01:06:52.690
even if their own lives
are in danger.

995
01:06:52.724 --> 01:06:53.758
Here. I'll show you.

996
01:06:53.791 --> 01:06:54.792
(engine accelerates)

997
01:06:54.826 --> 01:06:55.627
(tires screech)

998
01:06:55.660 --> 01:06:56.794
(horn beeps)

999
01:06:58.696 --> 01:07:00.030
(horn honks)

1000
01:07:00.063 --> 01:07:01.799
(horn blares. tires screech)

1001
01:07:04.034 --> 01:07:05.837
(vehicle thudding)

1002
01:07:05.870 --> 01:07:06.604
(glass shatters)

1003
01:07:06.638 --> 01:07:08.071
(explosion)

1004
01:07:08.773 --> 01:07:10.440
See what happened?

1005
01:07:10.474 --> 01:07:12.010
That car.

1006
01:07:12.042 --> 01:07:13.110
when we went into their lane.

1007
01:07:13.143 --> 01:07:14.378
instead of just
crossing the line

1008
01:07:14.411 --> 01:07:17.147
and breaking the law
and going into our lane.

1009
01:07:17.180 --> 01:07:20.150
they went into a ditch
and most likely died.

1010
01:07:21.451 --> 01:07:22.252
(birds chirping)

1011
01:07:22.286 --> 01:07:24.488
(indistinct radio chatter)

1012
01:07:36.266 --> 01:07:38.468
(indistinct speaking)

1013
01:08:00.525 --> 01:08:01.726
(sighs)

1014
01:08:01.759 --> 01:08:04.028
You smell that. Your Honor?

1015
01:08:04.062 --> 01:08:06.564
That's that good
clean country air.

1016
01:08:12.469 --> 01:08:14.204
I'd like to show you something.

1017
01:08:17.041 --> 01:08:19.443
(typing)

1018
01:08:21.512 --> 01:08:22.479
Look.

1019
01:08:23.447 --> 01:08:24.381
That's you.

1020
01:08:26.985 --> 01:08:27.952
Get away. get away.

1021
01:08:27.986 --> 01:08:29.286
(device beeping)

1022
01:08:29.319 --> 01:08:30.888
Let's see what you had to say.

1023
01:08:30.922 --> 01:08:33.558
Right. this is all
I have prepared.

1024
01:08:33.591 --> 01:08:35.693
and this is all that
I'm going to say to you.

1025
01:08:36.761 --> 01:08:40.598
Our politics fail
to integrate teenage migrants

1026
01:08:40.632 --> 01:08:42.366
into our society.

1027
01:08:42.399 --> 01:08:44.368
Also didn't give them
the help to function

1028
01:08:44.401 --> 01:08:47.437
by our rules and our laws.

1029
01:08:47.471 --> 01:08:51.709
The gang rape was. in a way.
a cry for help and structure.

1030
01:08:52.543 --> 01:08:55.312
Not only the young girl
is the victim.

1031
01:08:55.345 --> 01:08:56.881
They are also victims.

1032
01:08:59.149 --> 01:09:01.418
You really believe that?

1033
01:09:01.451 --> 01:09:04.254
Also the perpetrators
are getting traumatized.

1034
01:09:04.287 --> 01:09:05.957
It doesn't help
the young girl

1035
01:09:05.990 --> 01:09:07.892
if they're getting
locked up now.

1036
01:09:07.925 --> 01:09:11.495
and getting their normal life
for a long time denied.

1037
01:09:13.330 --> 01:09:14.766
That's all. gentlemen.

1038
01:09:17.501 --> 01:09:19.671
That was you

1039
01:09:19.704 --> 01:09:23.173
after letting
a gang of rapists free.

1040
01:09:24.142 --> 01:09:26.343
(car chiming)

1041
01:09:55.573 --> 01:09:58.375
You let a gang of rapists go.

1042
01:10:01.546 --> 01:10:02.914
You know what that makes you?

1043
01:10:04.314 --> 01:10:06.751
Just as bad
as the perpetrators.

1044
01:10:09.721 --> 01:10:11.254
Might as well
have raped her yourself.

1045
01:10:11.288 --> 01:10:12.990
Maybe that's why
you decided...

1046
01:10:14.424 --> 01:10:18.563
to come out here
and drown your sorrows.

1047
01:10:19.697 --> 01:10:21.699
(liquid glugging)

1048
01:10:26.804 --> 01:10:27.638
(knife clicks)

1049
01:10:51.696 --> 01:10:53.698
(engine starts)

1050
01:10:58.002 --> 01:11:00.004
(tense music)

1051
01:11:39.076 --> 01:11:41.311
(conversing in Arabic)

1052
01:11:46.884 --> 01:11:47.885
(knocking at door)

1053
01:11:47.919 --> 01:11:48.920
(doorbell chimes)

1054
01:11:48.953 --> 01:11:50.955
(conversing in Arabic)

1055
01:12:06.103 --> 01:12:07.205
Hello. Ibrahim.

1056
01:12:07.238 --> 01:12:08.506
Blessings to you
and your family.

1057
01:12:08.539 --> 01:12:10.007
I was wondering
if we could have a quick chat

1058
01:12:10.041 --> 01:12:10.942
about your son.

1059
01:12:10.975 --> 01:12:12.143
Are you a journalist?

1060
01:12:12.176 --> 01:12:14.278
No. I'm just a citizen.

1061
01:12:14.312 --> 01:12:15.546
Here to help.

1062
01:12:15.580 --> 01:12:18.216
If you want something.
you can go to our lawyer.

1063
01:12:18.249 --> 01:12:19.650
We don't have nothing to say.

1064
01:12:19.684 --> 01:12:20.751
Sorry.

1065
01:12:20.785 --> 01:12:23.688
Maybe we have
just a little chat.

1066
01:12:23.721 --> 01:12:24.755
(gun clicks)

1067
01:12:24.789 --> 01:12:25.656
Back.

1068
01:12:27.457 --> 01:12:28.593
(door slams)

1069
01:12:30.995 --> 01:12:31.596
(gasps)

1070
01:12:31.629 --> 01:12:33.463
Oh. good. Yusuf's here.

1071
01:12:34.031 --> 01:12:35.566
Relax. Go.

1072
01:12:37.768 --> 01:12:38.302
Hello. Yusuf.

1073
01:12:38.336 --> 01:12:39.604
Yusuf. run.

1074
01:12:39.637 --> 01:12:40.838
Where are they gonna go?

1075
01:12:40.872 --> 01:12:42.139
No. No. stop.

1076
01:12:42.173 --> 01:12:42.974
(gunshot)

1077
01:12:43.007 --> 01:12:45.009
(screaming. shrieking)

1078
01:12:46.277 --> 01:12:47.410
What are you doing?

1079
01:12:47.444 --> 01:12:49.146
-Yusuf. honey!
-Oh. Yusuf!

1080
01:12:49.180 --> 01:12:50.480
Go tend to your son.

1081
01:12:51.315 --> 01:12:52.415
